    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-15T16:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-15T16:30:00-05:00" n="195"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/5438: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-15T17:00:00-04:30"
                            >May 15, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>630. My 628 and 629.<note n="86" xml:id="d195fn86">Neither telegram
                        printed.</note> I have just received confirmation at the Foreign Office of
                    the resignation of the entire Cabinet. Reports from other sources say that Largo
                    Caballero has been requested to form a new Ministry. The city in general is
                    unaware of it and is quiet.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Ambassador Bowers and Embassy at Paris.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
